<DOC><DOCNO> AP880722-0235 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-22-88 2245EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Brazil-Hostage     07-22 0205</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Brazil-Hostage,0212</SECOND><HEAD>Bank Robbers Hold Boy Hostage in 10-Hour Ordeal</HEAD><HEAD>LaserPhoto RIO1</HEAD><DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two men surprised by police duringan attempted bank robbery took a 13-year-old boy hostage and ledpolice on a 60-mile chase before surrendering early Friday, statepolice said.   No one was injured in the incident.   Law enforcement officials interrupted the attempted bank robberyThursday in the mountain resort town of Teresopolis, 60 milesnortheast of Rio de Janeiro, police said.   Police said the two suspects fled to a nearby farmhouse and tookthe boy, identified as Andre Luiz Santarrita, hostage. Livetelevision footage showed one of the robbers holding two pistols tothe child's head and pleading with police surrounding the house notto invade.   After 10 hours, the boy was released in exchange for five otherhostages, including a police chief and journalists.   Early Friday, the two fled with the hostages in a car and werechased by police along the winding mountain road to Rio. Thehostages were released in Rio, and the robbers were trapped bypolice and surrendered.   Rio de Janeiro state police said the two men, identified only asMauro and Rogerio, were in police custody in Rio Friday night.</TEXT></DOC>